<item>
            <title>[LU-6150] gerrit: enable file search clause</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6150</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Gerrit 2.8.5 (current version on review.whamcloud.com) supports a search clause, &quot;file:&quot; that enables one to find patches that affect a specified file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would be useful, among other things, for finding others working in a given area, and for finding a changeset when you know the area but don&apos;t recall who was working on it or exactly when.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gerrit-documentation.storage.googleapis.com/Documentation/2.8.5/user-search.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gerrit-documentation.storage.googleapis.com/Documentation/2.8.5/user-search.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I used it on review.whamcloud.com, it responded that a secondary index needed to be enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you look into enabling this feature?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Olaf&lt;/p&gt;</description>
